review_blob: Lacks the strong coriander taste of most similar-style beers, which is a refreshing break from the Hefe norm in my opinion.  Tasty and drinkable.
The waiter at Hog Haus said it was 13%... that seemed high, but it had a pretty similar alcohol undertone/ aroma (and result) as when I tried Rochefort 10, which I believe is somewhere around 12%.
